# Profile narrative (template)

Copy this to `context/profile.md` and fill it in. This file is gitignored — it
holds the long-form prose the scorer and crafter use. Structured facts (titles,
comp, preferences) live in `config/config.yml` instead.

## Summary variants

A few framings of who you are, for different role types.

- **AI/Security leadership:** _e.g._ "Senior leader who builds and scales AI and
  security programs..."
- **Technical program management:** _..._
- **Individual-contributor / hands-on:** _..._

## Accomplishments

Concrete, quantified wins. The crafter draws on these; only true facts.

- Led X that achieved Y, measured by Z.
- Built/shipped/scaled ... resulting in ...

## Voice & cover-letter style

How you write. Phrases you use, tone, things to avoid (no clichés, no corporate
filler). The cover-letter generator mirrors this.

- Direct, specific, evidence-first.
- Avoid: "passionate", "synergy", "fast-paced", "wear many hats".
